			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-4352" title="">August 10th, 2006 at 15:09 +0000 (UTC)</a> </small>

			<p>Personally I'm not a big fan of "continue" and "break". I think it obfuscates the flow of logic. Using your example above, why not do this:</p>
<p>var arr = ["dog", "cat"];<br />
var action = 'greet';<br />
for(i = 0, ln = arr.length; i &lt; ln; i++) {<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;animal = arr[i];<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (animal == "cat") alert("hello " + animal);<br />
}</p>
<p>Here we have a one line if condition, so no extra indention is necessary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Plus without the "continue" the code is easier to read.</p>

		</li>

	
	
		<li class=" commentOfficialUser" id="comment-4353">
