As always with programming: don't religiously stick to such rules. Just be consistent.</p>
<p>Also, for continue it could make more sense to define it positively and negate the whole thing. This is often easier to understand.<br />
<code><br />
if (!(animal == 'cat')) continue;<br />
</code></p>
