			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-4425" title="">August 13th, 2006 at 10:47 +0000 (UTC)</a> </small>

			<p>I disagree with Jack and Dean: even when a post from an untrusted source contains some bad practices, often the right way is pointed out in some of the comments, together with interesting links. So, this kind of discussions enrich anyway my knowledge. And it's also useful in order to distinguish between trusted (as Dean's blog) and untrusted sources.</p>

